                        <item xml:id="a1"> <locus target="#7vb">f. 7vb</locus>
                           <desc>: Ownership note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"> <locus target="#7vb">7vb</locus>: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘወልደ፡ ኢየሱ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ለወልዱ፡ አትናቴዎስ፡ ወለእሙ፡  ወለተ፡ ማርያም።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"> <locus target="#7vb">7vb</locus>: This book belongs to Walda ʾIyäsu(s) who has given it to his son ʾAtnatewos and to his mother Walatta Māryām.</quote>
                           <note>
                           
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2"> <locus target="#23v">f. 23v</locus>
                           <desc>: Note on grain donations to the church.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           In Amharic. The note mentions rās<note> Walda Śǝllāse.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3"> <locus target="#25vb">f. 25vb</locus>
                           <desc>: Note on grain donations to the church.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           In Amharic. Incomplete. The note mentions rās Wäräñña and nǝguś<note> Yoḥannǝs.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4"> <locus target="#172vb">f. 172vb</locus>
                           <desc>: Supplication for the owner of the Ms. and for his relatives.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"> <locus target="#172vb">172vb</locus>: በረከቶሙ፡ ለአበዊነ፡ ሐዋርያት፡ የሀሉ፡ ምስለ፡ ፍቁሮሙ፡ ወልደ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ወለወልዱ፡ አትናቴዎስ፡ ወለእሙ፡ ወለተ፡ ማርያም። ዘአንበብክዋ፡ ለዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ኢትርስኡነ፡ አቡነ፡ ዘበሰማያት።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"> <locus target="#172vb">172vb</locus>: May the blessing of our fathers the Apostles be with their beloved Walda ʾIyasus, and with his son ʾAtnatewos, and with his mother Walatta Māryām. You who read this book, do not forget us; (recite for us) the Paternoster.</quote>
                           <note>
                           
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Two apparently recent marginal notes: ዘደብረ ጽዮን ቅድስት ማርያም መጽሓፈ ቅዳሴ and ደብረ ጽዮን ቅድስት ማርያም ቤተ ክርስቲያን ዘብሄረ ነቢያት።: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>.&#xD;
- Crude drawings of crosses in the margins: <locus target="#17r">17r</locus>, 28v, 40r, 69r, 87r, 88r,&#xD;
- Notes (mostly crude) in the upper margin: <locus target="#17v">17v</locus>, 33v, 43v, 46r, 46v, etc.&#xD;
C- rude notes in the right-hand margin (writing exercise): <locus target="#101r">101r</locus>.&#xD;
- Pieces of parchment possibly originating from different Mss., sewn onto the leaves, with text: <locus target="#38v">38v</locus>, 43r.&#xD;
- Ms. of smaller size sewn on to the leaf. The Ms. consists of 3 folios and contains prayers from the Ordinary of the Mass: <locus target="#64r">64r</locus>.&#xD;
- Parchment stripe sewn on to the leaf: <locus target="#43v">43v</locus>.&#xD;
- Part of the Anaphora of St Epiphanius, crudely written in brown ink: <locus target="#151r">151r</locus>, in the upper margin, 151va-vb, 152r, in the upper and right-hand margins.&#xD;
- Arithmetical calculation (1984 – 996 = 988) written in European digits: <locus target="#176vb">176vb</locus>.</item>
